In his new edition of the fragments of the Tragic poets, Prof. Ribbeck bows to the authority of Ritschl and enriches his fragments with a number of final d, even giving Pacuvius his share of them. It is, therefore, very probable that he will join Nonius and Ritschl in believing in a nom. plur. laetitias, though Bucheler (Lac. Dec-Z. p. 17) and Corssen 1 p. 754 are strongly opposed to it.
